The paper focuses on using smart watch sensor data to infer an individual's emotional state, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The study also involves the use of machine learning techniques to classify emotions based on sensor data, which is a common topic in the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the study involves the analysis of time series data, which falls under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY). The use of audiovisual and audio stimuli also suggests a potential connection to the sound (cs.SD) sub-category. Finally, the study involves the use of wearable technology, which is a common topic in the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
